tool.name: NumberFeatures

param.name: input_area_features
param.dialogReference: Select an existing area layer from the map or use the input_area_features tool to sketch an area on the map.

param.name: input_point_features
param.dialogReference: The features in the map to be numbered.

param.name: field_to_number
param.dialogReference: Select a field in Features to Number used to number, or re-number. If nothing is selected a new field named Number will be added.

param.name: output_features
param.dialogReference: Select a new numbered output features. If nothing is selected the Features to Number will be used.

tool.summary: Number Features will add numbers to a field in an existing feature class. If the extent of the Area to Number does not include all of the features in the target feature class, and if you do no specify a new output feature class, the features outside of the Area to Number will be deleted.
tool.usage:
• Only features from Features to Number that fall within the selected Input Area to Number will be numbered.

  • If Field to Number is not selected a new Number (short) field will be added to the Output Numbered Features.

  • If Output Numbered Features is not specified the input Features to Number will be updated.

  • Features are numbered sequentially from top to bottom, and from left to right.
